From: NuttX RP2350 maintainers <noreply@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] examples/ftpd: do not log every successful session

The FTP daemon writes a status line to stdout after every successful client.
On boards where stdout is a bounded USB CDC console with no active reader,
rapid sessions fill the console buffer and block the daemon before its next
accept.  Treat success as the normal silent path and retain diagnostics for
actual errors.

---
 examples/ftpd/ftpd_main.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/examples/ftpd/ftpd_main.c b/examples/ftpd/ftpd_main.c
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/examples/ftpd/ftpd_main.c
+++ b/examples/ftpd/ftpd_main.c
@@ -292,11 +292,11 @@ static int ftpd_daemon(int argc, FAR char *argv[])
           break;
         }
 
-      /* If any interesting happened (i.e., any thing other than a timeout),
-       * then report the interesting event.
+      /* Successful session startup and idle timeouts are normal.  Report
+       * unexpected errors only.
        */
 
-      if (ret != -ETIMEDOUT)
+      if (ret < 0 && ret != -ETIMEDOUT)
         {
           printf("FTP daemon [%d] ftpd_session returned %d\n",
                  pid, ret);
